+ export const updateCategoryDescription = async (id: string, description: string) =&gt; {
+     try {
+         const { error } = await supabaseAdmin
+             .from('categories')
+             .update({ description })
+             .eq('id', id);
+             
+         if (error) throw error;
+         return { success: true };
+     } catch (e: any) {
+         return { success: false, error: e.message };
+     }
+ };

+ export const updateCategoryDescription = async (id: string, description: string) =&gt; {
+     try {
+         const { error } = await supabaseAdmin
+             .from('categories')
+             .update({ description })
+             .eq('id', id);
+             
+         if (error) throw error;
+         return { success: true };
+     } catch (e: any) {
+         return { success: false, error: e.message };
+     }
+ };

I have updated the application to allow creating categories with descriptions.

1.  **Updated `createCategory` in `src/lib/categoryService.ts`** to accept an optional `description` parameter.
2.  **Updated Inventory Manager (`/admin/inventory`)**:
    *   Added a description textarea to the "New Category" modal.
    *   Passed the description to the create function.
3.  **Updated Category Manager (`/admin/categories`)**:
    *   Added a description textarea below the category name input in the creation sidebar.
    *   Updated the creation handler to include the description.

You can now add descriptions when creating new categories in both admin interfaces.
